		   <table class="mform"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%" >
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2">Taunt Duel Wield vs 2H<br clear="all" /><script type="text/javascript">document.title = document.title + ": Thread: Taunt Duel Wield vs 2H";</script>
		   <span class="sm">Posted: Fri, Sep 2nd 3:21 AM 2005 EST</span><span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=1;mid=112564616115487423;num=22;page=1;post=1;replyto=112564616115487423"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a>    <a name="112564616115487423"></a></span></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" class="mform" ><span class="fs8"><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=225574"><span class="">Madipides</span></a><b><span class=""></span></b><br />5 posts
		   <br /><span class="nobr"><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent  </span><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist;addname=Madipides;type=Address" class="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book" /> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1" alt=""/></span></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>Hey all, <br /> <br />I just had a wierd experience that shook my views regarding the best taunt weapons.&nbsp;&nbsp;My 59 warrior had been in retirement, until I dusted him off the last couple days.  Tonight I put up my LFG and had a very unexpected invite..they wanted me to tank in WOS at lvl 59!  They were desperate, but I went anyway just to see how I would do (and my expedient recovery was unused and available). <br /> <br />Well I actually could tank them, sort of, but that's not the point of this post.  Finally a lvl 62 paladin came along, so I switched from my max taunt bandolier to a 2hs dps weapon.  For max aggro I currently use a Wind Worn Handblade and a Sword of the Bloodsworn, like 12/18 and 12/19 both with a proc, one has a dd and one has a stun.  OK so I switched to my War Marshall's Bladed Staff which is 31/28 with no proc.   <br /> <br />OK, here's the problem.  Whenever I equipped my War Marshall's Staff, the mob turned back to me.  So then I would switch to the duel wield with proc configuration, and I would lose the aggro.  This happened like 3 times.  I don't know if it was a gimpy paladin, but he was 3 levels higher than me, so gear should be a non-issue.  And I dont know how well he was stunning either.  I was pulling, rather than he, so that might skew the taunt toward me some.  But I was not taunting or bellowing at all. <br /> <br />So what do you think....War Marshall's Staff with no augment was out-taunting my Sword of the Bloodsworn and Wind Worn Handblade (and I have weapon affinity 1, plus have the shorter delay one in primary like a good warrior would do). <br /> <br />Madipides 70 Naturewalker <br />Eltrab 59 Myrmidon <br />Tongah 52 Brawler <br />Milnor 44 Magician <br />on the Luclin Server</p>
<br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Madipides 70 Naturewalker <br />Eltrab 59 Myrmidon <br />Tongah 52 Brawler <br />Milnor 44 Magician <br />on the Luclin Server</td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td class="fs8"></td><td align="right" class="fs8" >22 Replies</td></tr></table>
</td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td>

		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%" >
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2">
		   <span class="sm">Posted: Fri, Sep 2nd 5:19 AM 2005 EST</span><span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=1;mid=112564616115487423;num=22;page=1;post=1;replyto=1125653212154291811"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a>    <a name="1125653212154291811"></a></span></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" class="mform2" ><span class="fs8"><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=404101"><span class="">intcasta</span></a><b><span class=""></span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />130 posts
		   <br /><span class="nobr"><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent  </span><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist;addname=intcasta;type=Address" class="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book" /> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1" alt=""/></span></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>I have heard two schools of thought on this issue: <br /> <br /> <br />1. The more often you hit the more you get agro, independent of how hard you are hitting <br />2. The more melee damage you do the more you get agro, independent of hit speed <br /> <br /> <br />Nobody in-game that I have spoken with knows for certain which is true. I would really love to know, and I think most people generally side with statement one. That is how I play my warrior, using 2hs for when I am not tanking and dual wielding when I am trying to maintain agro. <br /> <br /> <br />It is interesting to note that some weapons' stun procs (specifically those with that planar stun iirc) actually have a built-in agro reducing property. They stun (which increases hate) and they also lower hate directly. I have not looked into it enough to know whether the proc reduces hate further than the stun raises it; the net result of the stun and hate lowering remains unknown to me. I would not expect this was the cause of your unusual agro situation though.</p>
