		   <span class="sm">Posted: Fri, Sep 2nd 4:45 PM 2005 EST</span><span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=1;mid=112564616115487423;num=22;page=1;post=1;replyto=1125694409114391473"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a>    <a name="1125694409114391473"></a></span></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" class="mform2" ><span class="fs8"><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=313551"><span class="">WarriorJoe</span></a><b><span class=""></span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />265 posts
		   <br /><span class="nobr"><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Default  </span><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist;addname=WarriorJoe;type=Address" class="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book" /> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1" alt=""/></span></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p>Who holds aggro is a function of a number of parameters.&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />One of the parameters could be called weapons generated hate.   <br />The major factor (not including procs) in deciding how much hate your weapon generates is how much damage it can do and how often it dose that damage.  <br />Some folks like to think about this as the amount of hate generated per swing.   <br /> <br />In your example you seems to be generating more hate with  your 2hs than with your normal high aggro combo.  Some factors that could lead to this are as follows. <br /> <br />1. Due to the higher damage bonus for two handed weapons you are doing more damage, this factor can play a signifent role due to dubble attack etc.  A dubble attack with a two handed weapon generates a lot more hate than a dubble attack with a one handed weapon.  This would be even more of a factor fighting high lvl (red) mobs which are harder for you to hit with your off hand, and thus your off hand weapon isn't adding as much hate as you might expect.   <br /> <br />2. You dex might be low enough that you are not getting a lot of procs from your weapons, and therefore you don't get the amount of hate you expect, this is even more likly if you don't have any aa to increasses your proc rate.   <br /> <br /> <br />The fact that you out aggroed the Knight can be explaned along the same lines.   <br />Odds are the mobs in WoS were red to him as well, so his extra 3 levels didn't give him a lot in the way of getting more hits than you.  In fact with your higher melee skill and better tables  you might of been hitting on a higher percent of your swings.  <br />The Knight was probaly generating less hate with his weapons than he thought.  His frequency of casting stun is based on fighting blue mobs, and thus was not often enough to stay ahead of you on the hate list while fighting high lvl mobs.  <br /> <br />So to sum it up <br />It is easier to hit a high lvl mob with your primary than with your off hand.   <br />Using a two hand weapon generates more hate than the same calaber one hand weapon in the primary slot (do to damage bonus). <br />Depending on dex you might not be getting the number of proc you think. <br />Knights generate less melee hate than warriors do.  <br /> <br /></p>
