		   <span class="sm">Posted: Sat, Sep 3rd 10:29 AM 2005 EST</span><span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/db/classes.html?class=1;mid=112564616115487423;num=22;page=1;post=1;replyto=1125758210186276614"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a>    <a name="1125758210186276614"></a></span></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" class="mform2" ><span class="fs8"><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=184366"><span class="Scholar">dfrnchman</span></a><b><span class="Scholar"><br/>Scholar</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />860 posts
		   <br /><span class="nobr"><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Decent  </span><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist;addname=dfrnchman;type=Address" class="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book" /> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1" alt=""/></span></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p><blockquote><b class="sm">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />Can you explain this a bit more if you don't mind? Apparently there's something about stunning that I didn't know about.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /> <br />Is it that stun aggro remains constant, while melee aggro is dependent upon (amount of damage X delay)?  And with red mobs you miss more, so your damage is lesser. Or is it more of a damage in relationship of mob's hps? Or am I totally wrong? Hehe sorry, just trying to learn more about it now that I'm playing my warrior more. <hr size="1" /></blockquote>  <br />While procced stuns generally generate a consistant amount of hate, usually around 400, cast stuns work much different.  <br />The hate generated by ANY cast stun, regardless of the spell level, is based on the maximum number of hitpoints the paticular mob CAN have. Note this is CAN have and not the actual amount is DOES have. There is also a cap to the amount of hate a cast stun can generate, which you start bumping into around the mid 60s level mobs. A cast stun cannot generate more than about 1300 hate. Generally, this cap only really comes into play ATM in the very high end (MPG trials, Anguish), but might start becoming more of a problem if SOE doesnt change something. The pally boards in the SoE forums are full of this concern.</p>
