		   <tr><td valign="top" class="mform" ><span class="fs8"><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=459747"><span class="">Anez</span></a><b><span class=""></span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />138 posts
		   <br /><span class="nobr"><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Default  </span><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist;addname=Anez;type=Address" class="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book" /> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1" alt=""/></span></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%">
<p>Stun does the same amount of hate each time it's cast. There is no progression to them, which in higher level con area's can make aggro a bit difficult to Pally's. I have found that I actually have to hold off a bit, while Pally's get a second, or even a 3rd stun in, when slowing the mobs with my Chanter. After a 3rd stun (back to back) it's pretty hard to take aggro away from a Pally, unless your trying to.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br /> <br />I think the question of using the 2h weapon in red con territory was answered very well. We (Warrior's) used to use 2h weapons in high level zones alot before such emphasis was put on Augmentations, and Enraging blow, Hate based proc's, etc. DPS helps aggro alot more then I think is currently believed by most boards. When fighting Red Cons, your weapon's proc alot less, ussually. When fighting even and lower cons, alot of stuff seems to work better, including Taunt.  <br /> <br />Also, a three level difference is not that big of deal if the mobs are red to both of you.  <br /> <br />I would like to know, if you noticed how much the Pally was stunning while tanking in WOS. I have noticed some Pally's that lose aggro while stunning, cuz other's jump the gun (Hit the mob before the Pally actually engages). Ussually two stuns can hold aggro from other mellee quite well, when cast back to back.</p>
