<p><blockquote><b class="sm">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />Stun does the same amount of hate each time it's cast. There is no progression to them, which in higher level con area's can make aggro a bit difficult to Pally's.<hr size="1" /></blockquote> <br />Incorrect. It does scale and has been parsed to that effect, not to mention all but confirmed by the devs. If it was a set hate, 2 or 3 stuns by my level 70 paladin would give me enough aggro that my level 14 druid would never get it nack. This is not the case. My druid will yank aggro back after just 2 or 3 whacks with her club and a spell or 2. <br />The difficulty in the high end is, as I mentioned, that stuns do have a cap to the hate they create, which is around 1300. Paladins in anguish have frequently complained about it as they can chain stun with 3 stuns and still not hold aggro because of the insane DPS their guildmates can generate.</p>
