		   <tr><td valign="top" class="mform2" ><span class="fs8"><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=410981"><span class="">Mashor</span></a><b><span class=""></span></b><br />9 posts
		   <br /><span class="nobr"><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good  </span><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist;addname=Mashor;type=Address" class="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book" /> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1" alt=""/></span></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p><blockquote><b class="sm">Quote:</b><hr size="1" /> Agro is generated by potential dps and not dps itself.<hr size="1" /></blockquote> <br /> <br /><blockquote><b class="sm">Necrophobe wrote:</b><hr size="1" />[quote] I've never heard this (ever).&nbsp;&nbsp;If that were the case, I could hold agro forever with the aug'd Dalthor's Great Hammer that I've used in PvP duels jousting (that hammer sux tanking mobs).<hr size="1" /></blockquote>   <br /> <br />  This is the accepted theory on DPS aggro and it is easily proven.  As soon as I pop defensive on a raid mob and cut my dps to 50% of normal I would lose aggro very fast regardless of procs, bellow effects or any other trick that can be pulled out of the hat.  Procs play a large factor in aggro generation but swing aggro is also quite large and if the game was counting actual dps rather than potential weapon dps you would never see a warrior hold aggro on raid boss fights for the full 3 minutes that the defensive disc is up.   <br /> <br />  Another example is mobs that are totally/partialy immume to weapon damage or need bane weapons to damage.  Warrior will engage these with their regular tanking weapons and hold aggro throughout the fight while actually doing little to 0 DPS.  Examples include Seru, Emperor Ssraeshza, Cragbeast Queen and I often will tank the Master of Ingenity for some of the fight with my epic and DBoTW to build aggro and gain survivabilty.  Threads about this subject are too numerous to quote on thesteelwarrior.org but a search will yield many of them to you. <br /> </p>
