		   <tr><td valign="top" class="mform2" ><span class="fs8"><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=313551"><span class="">WarriorJoe</span></a><b><span class=""></span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />265 posts
		   <br /><span class="nobr"><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Default  </span><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist;addname=WarriorJoe;type=Address" class="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book" /> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1" alt=""/></span></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%">
<p><blockquote><b class="sm">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />Agro is generated by potential dps and not dps itself. You will get the same agro from max hits to no hits at all as long as the weapons have the same delay and damage bonus.&nbsp;&nbsp;<hr size="1" /></blockquote> <br /> <br />This is the acepted theroy of weapon generated hate... according to the group over on Steal Warrior.   <br />It is based on an experment done where a spell of know hate was cast on a mob and then the melee class attacked the mob from behind.  The experiment was done with a number of different weapons, and it was found that the mob truned to face the weapon user after ABOUT the same number of swings of the same weapon or set of weapons.  Yes I said ABOUT.  And the DIFFERANCE in the number of swings it took to turn the mob increassed with the damage of the weapon.  Now if you ask me, if the theroy was 100% right the mob should turn after the exact same number of swings for the same weapon everytime. <br /> <br /> <br /><blockquote><b class="sm">Quote:</b><hr size="1" />If you dont believe me, do the following. Equip your highest DPS weapon. Have a tank buddy pull a DB mob and tank him with a rusty weapon for a couple of minutes (not using taunts or spells). Then attack the mob yourself. You should have the mob turn on you as soon as you attack (not when the first hit lands) if your theory on potential DPS is true. <hr size="1" /></blockquote> <br /> <br />A number of experiments have been done that suggest that Hate as a function of potencial damage per swig cannot explane all experimental results, or observations.   <br /> <br /><blockquote><b class="sm">Quote:</b><hr size="1" /> Another example is mobs that are totally/partialy immume to weapon damage or need bane weapons to damage. Warrior will engage these with their regular tanking weapons and hold aggro throughout the fight while actually doing little to 0 DPS. Examples include Seru, Emperor Ssraeshza, <hr size="1" /></blockquote> <br />This kind of arguemnt lends support to the theroy, however the same folks (over at SW) regulary suggest that hate from proc has a larger effect than hate from weapons dps.  In fact they suggest that you get WA asap to help you hold aggro in just such instances.  And as I recall, the damage done by the bane weapons was rather poor, and to my knowlage noone ever put any porc on them. <br /> <br /> <br />In spite of the fact that this theroy is supported by SW, it can not explane all experimental results nor can it explane all observations, therefore it cannot be accepted as the complete truth concerning how weapons damage hate is determined.  <br /> <br />There is no differance with which weapons are best for generating hate if you assume dps or if you assume hate per swing.  This is due to the fact that the hate per swing  theroy has been improved to take into account evrything that increasses actual damage.  For example if you take two warrior of slightly different levels but with identacal equipment, the higher one holds aggro most of the time. To account for this the hate per swing folks added a  fator for level in the rather comberson equation used to calculate how much hate is generated per swing. <br /> <br />In the end, what most warriors want to know is which weapon give  the most hate generation.  And using dps come to this answer in a faster and easier to understand way.</p>
